definition.value: A sulfonium compound that is the conjugate acid of S-methyl-L-methioninate.
Decaanion of 1D-myo-inositol 1,2,3,4,5-pentakisphosphate arising from global deprotonation of the phosphate groups.

A member of the class of indazoles that is 2H-indazole substituted by 4-(piperidin-3-yl)phenyl and aminocarbonyl groups at positions 2 and 7, respectively. It is a potent PARP1 inhibitor with IC50 of 3.2 nM.
A 2-[4-(piperidin-3-yl)phenyl]-2H-indazole-7-carboxamide that has R-configuration. It is a potent PARP1 inhibitor with IC50 of 2.4 nM.
